President Biden spoke with Florida Governor Ron DeSantis to offer support after approving an emergency declaration for Miami-Dade County following the partial collapse of a residential building in Surfside. The President expressed gratitude for first responders and search and rescue teams, as well as condolences to the governor and the Surfside community. The emergency declaration authorizes FEMA to provide disaster relief, coordinate efforts, and offer temporary shelter and housing. FEMA has deployed teams and experts to assist in the response. The White House and FEMA are closely coordinating with local officials, and the President will receive regular updates.